div.p:
In that Logestilla giueth Astolfo at his departing a booke to instruct him, and a horne to breed terror to his enemies;
                  Allegorie.
                by the booke is signified wisedome, whereby all charmes and toyes are discouered: and by the horne is vnderstood iustice, that indeed brings terror to all misdoers, and driues them out of the country. Further, whereas Logestilla sends Andronica and Sophrosina to safe conduct Astolfo, least Aleyna should attempt any new matter against him, it is to be vnderstood allegorically, that fortitude and temperance are the two most notable guides that we can haue in this world to keepe vs from pleasures snares, or violent assaults. Also whereas Astolfo looks first in his booke ere he take vpon him the enterprise to fight with Orillus, it is to be vnderstood, that good aduice is to be taken before men vndertake dangerous exploits.

